You can adjust the size of the chess board by modifying the `width` and `height` options of the `\chessboard` command. For example, to make the board wider, you could use something like `\chessboard[fen=#1,width=12cm]`.

Note that this example assumes that you have installed the `chessboard` package on your LaTeX distribution. If you don't have it installed, you may need to download and install it separately before you can use it.

